Product Requirements Document (PRD): BidPilot MVP
Version: 2.0 (Full Suite)
Date: 2025-11-23
Status: High-Fidelity MVP for Hackathon Submission
Executive Summary
BidPilot is an agentic AI ecosystem that disrupts the $3.1B Proposal Software market. Unlike competitors (Loopio, AutoRFP) that require manual library maintenance ("Garbage In, Garbage Out"), BidPilot offers Autonomous "Zero-Touch" Operations. It matches competitor feature sets (Content Library, Drafting, Compliance) but executes them using autonomous agents, requiring 90% fewer human hours to setup and operate.
The "Smart" Differentiator (The "Why Us")
We deliver feature parity with "Lesser Resources" through Agentic Intelligence:
Competitors: Require humans to manually tag and curate a "Q&A Library".
BidPilot: Uses "The Historian" & "The Shredder" to ingest raw data (Google Drive/SharePoint) and autonomously index "Company Knowledge" without human tagging.
Competitors: Use RAG (Search) which fails on complex reasoning.
BidPilot: Uses Gemini 3.0 Long Context to read entire project histories, ensuring deep consistency.
MVP Scope: The "Full Stack" Autonomous Suite
This MVP demonstrates a complete end-to-end workflow that replaces the entire proposal team:
Autonomous Ingestion (The Historian): Connects to raw storage and instantly creates a "Knowledge Graph".
The Gatekeeper (Go/No-Go): The "Kill Switch" to prevent wasted work.
The Architect (Drafting): Generates full executive summaries and answers based on historical style.
The Quant (Excel/Security): Automates the tedious security spreadsheets using Python Code Execution.
The Auditor (Compliance): Checks the final output against RFP constraints.
Agent Specifications (The Swarm)
A. The Historian (Knowledge Core)
Role: Autonomous Librarian.
Capabilities: Ingests raw PDFs/Docs. Indexes "Winning Answers", "Case Studies", and "Team Bios" automatically.
Smart Factor: Zero manual tagging required.
B. The Gatekeeper (Logic Core)
Role: Risk Analyst.
Logic: Scans 100+ pages for deal-breakers (Budget, Tech Stack, Location).
Output: Hard "No-Go" signals to save time.
C. The Architect (Generative Core)
Role: Proposal Writer.
Capabilities: Style Transfer (mimics past winning proposals). Uses "Star Method" for case studies.
Smart Factor: Writes compliant content, not just generic text.
D. The Quant (Technical Core)
Role: Excel Automation Engineer.
Capabilities: Reads Excel Security Questionnaires. Writes Python code to fill "Yes/No" and "Comments" columns based on security docs.
E. The Auditor (Quality Core)
Role: Compliance Officer.
Capabilities: Validates font sizes, page limits, and mandatory keywords.
User Experience (UX) Flow
Mission Control: Dashboard showing ROI (Time Saved/Money Won).
Knowledge Base: Visual graph of ingested documents (proving "Zero Setup").
Live Analysis: The "Glass Box" terminal showing the Agent Swarm working in parallel.
Drafting Room: The final editor where the human polishes the Agent's work.
Technical Stack (Simulation)
Frontend: React, Tailwind CSS, Lucide React Icons.
UI Library: shadcn/ui aesthetic.
Agent Logic: Simulated State Machine with asynchronous delays to mimic multi-agent reasoning.
